{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/til/technical-writing/one/11-punctuation/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"bestalign's dev blog","categories":[{"displayText":"홈","priority":0,"name":"home","url":"/"},{"displayText":"TIL","priority":1,"name":"til","url":"/til"},{"displayText":"개발","priority":2,"name":"dev","url":"/dev"},{"displayText":"독서","priority":3,"name":"reading","url":"/reading"},{"displayText":"번역","priority":4,"name":"translation","url":"/translation"},{"displayText":"일기","priority":5,"name":"everydaylife","url":"/everydaylife"}]}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"8c6823a5-d83c-5d24-b3f1-e292cfc4f2ff","excerpt":"Commas 프로그래밍 언어와는 달리 영어의 comma 룰은 확실하지 않다. 문장을 읽다가 자연스럽게 잠깐 멈추는 곳에 comma를 넣어라. Embedded list item 사이에 comma를 넣어라. 조건문일 경우 조건과 결과 사이에 comma…","html":"<h4 id=\"commas\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#commas\" aria-label=\"commas permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Commas</h4>\n<p>프로그래밍 언어와는 달리 영어의 comma 룰은 확실하지 않다. 문장을 읽다가 자연스럽게 잠깐 멈추는 곳에 comma를 넣어라.</p>\n<p>Embedded list item 사이에 comma를 넣어라.</p>\n<p>조건문일 경우 조건과 결과 사이에 comma를 넣어라.</p>\n<p>문장 내에서 간단한 정의나 추가적인 설명을 끼워넣을 때에 comma로 감싸라.</p>\n<p>두 독립적인 문장을 comma로 연결하지마라. 이런 문법적 문제를 comma splice라고 부른다.</p>\n<h5 id=\"examples\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#examples\" aria-label=\"examples permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Examples</h5>\n<p>C behaves as a mid-level language, just a couple of steps up in abstraction from assembly language.</p>\n<p>Our company uses C++, Python, Java, and JavaScript.</p>\n<p>If the program runs slowly, then try the —perf flag.</p>\n<p>Python, an easy-to-use language, has gained significant momentum in recent years.</p>\n<h4 id=\"semicolons\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#semicolons\" aria-label=\"semicolons permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Semicolons</h4>\n<p>개별적인 문장은 마침표로 나누고 깊게 관련되어 있는 문장은 semicolon으로 연결하라.</p>\n<p>두 문장은 문법적으로 완벽한 문장이어야 하고 두 문장의 순서를 바꾸었을 때에도 말이 되어야 한다.</p>\n<p>semicolon 바로 뒤에 접속사/접속절을 넣을 수도 있다.</p>\n<h5 id=\"examples-1\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#examples-1\" aria-label=\"examples 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Examples</h5>\n<p>Rerun Frambus after updating your configuration file; don’t rerun Frambus after updating existing source code.</p>\n<p>Even seemingly trivial code changes can cause bugs; therefore, write abundant unit tests.</p>\n<h4 id=\"em-dashes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#em-dashes\" aria-label=\"em dashes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Em-Dashes</h4>\n<p>Em-dash은 comma보다 더 긴 멈춤을 나타내고 comma와 같은 역할을 한다. 둘의 정확한 용법상 차이점은 없다.</p>\n<h5 id=\"examples-2\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#examples-2\" aria-label=\"examples 2 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Examples</h5>\n<p>C++ is a rich language—one requiring extensive experience to master.</p>\n<p><strong>Protocol</strong> Buffers—often nicknamed <strong>protobufs</strong>—encode structured data in an efficient yet extensible format.</p>\n<h4 id=\"parenthesis\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#parenthesis\" aria-label=\"parenthesis permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Parenthesis</h4>\n<p>Parenthesis는 사소한 내용이나 문장을 끼워넣을 때 사용한다. 중요하지 않은 내용을 넣을 때 사용하므로 최소한으로 사용하는 게 좋다.</p>\n<p>문장 전체를 감쌀 때에는 마침표까지 같이 감싸고, 문장의 마지막에 부분적으로 넣을 때에는 마침표는 바깥에 표기하라.</p>\n<h5 id=\"examples-3\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#examples-3\" aria-label=\"examples 3 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Examples</h5>\n<p>(Incidentally, Protocol Buffers make great birthday gifts.)</p>\n<p>Binary mode relies on the more compact native form (described later in this document).</p>\n<h4 id=\"reference\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#reference\" aria-label=\"reference permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Reference</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://developers.google.com/tech-writing/one/punctuation\">Google Dev Technical Writing 1 - Punctuation</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"테크니컬 라이팅 - punctuation","category":"til","date":"July 17, 2021","updated":null,"description":null,"tags":["technical writing"]}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/til/technical-writing/one/10-documents/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"테크니컬 라이팅 - Documents"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/til/technical-writing/two/01-self-editing/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"테크니컬 라이팅 - Self-editing"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"8c6823a5-d83c-5d24-b3f1-e292cfc4f2ff","previousPostId":"bcc7c111-854c-5f1c-bdfa-7ba8d8c4b7b4","nextPostId":"dc8c5e27-049a-54d4-a9e7-6d3309583130"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383"]}